This paper deals with the performance analysis of the Joint Spatial Division and Multiplexing (JSDM) algorithm in mm-Wave channels. The paper discusses the optimization of user grouping for two different objectives, which involves graph-theoretic frameworks. These topics are closely related to the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer communications (cs.COM). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
